* Cache directives (Pragma: no-cache, and Cache-Control: no-cache)

* Referer directives to improve forward /context functionality

* Other headers at http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec14.html
  - Accept-Charset, Accept-Language, Content-Language
  - Age
  - Authorization, see also  WWW-Authenticate
  - Content-Location (with all MW redirection abilities, this could be useful...)
  - Content-MD5
  - If-Match
  - If-Range
  - If-Unmodified-Since
  - Max-Forwards (requires implementation of TRACE? OPTIONS?)

* Expect should return a 417 if something other than 100-continue is given

